race.comment: SNITZOND (3) is going well and looks nicely placed out in journey now. Fresh-up winner then fourth last two over sharper distances. Has performed well over 1200m and raced once to 1400m. Great record here and gets a chance to return to winning form. LINTHORPE LUCK (5) looks the biggest danger. Finally off the mark with a strong maiden win here last time. At peak fitness and expected to measure up again. MISS DE MEDICI (7) continues to race well including an effortless win last time at Warwick. This is tougher but drawn for a soft run and should be in the finish. REGGAE FIRE (2) is fitter for two runs back and will find this easier than the Class 3 at Doomben latest. Has had two runs for the new yard and having first try on the new home track tonight.
